<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
      i18n:domain="launchpad">

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-details" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-actions" />
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <h1>Reject Support Request</h1>

  <p class="documentDescription">
    If you believe that this request is a hoax, or a test, or sample data,
    and should not be listed in reports and forms, then use this form to
    reject it.
  </p>

  <p>
    We do not list rejected tickets in most reports. It is better to reject
    fake or bogus support requests than to mark them closed, because it
    gives a cleaner set of statistics.
  </p>

  <form action="." method="POST">

    <div class="actions">
      <input type="submit"
             name="cancel"
             value="Cancel" />
      <input tal:condition="context/can_be_rejected"
             type="submit"
             name="reject"
             value="Reject Ticket" />
    </div>

  </form>

</div>
</body>
</html>
